ght: 400;"> results.</span></p><h2><span id=3D"How_To_Use_the_Simpson8217s_=
Rule_Calculator">How To Use the Simpson=E2=80=99s Rule Calculator?</span></=
h2><p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">You can use the </span><b>Simpson=
=E2=80=99s Rule Calculator </b><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">by putting=
 the details of definite integrals in their respective boxes. After this, a=
 detailed solution will be presented in front of you</span><span style=3D"l=
etter-spacing: 1.2px; font-size: var( --e-global-typography-fd4917d-font-si=
ze ); word-spacing: var( --e-global-typography-fd4917d-word-spacing );">&nb=
sp;with just a single click</span><span style=3D"letter-spacing: var( --e-g=
lobal-typography-fd4917d-letter-spacing ); word-spacing: var( --e-global-ty=
pography-fd4917d-word-spacing );">.</span></p><p><span style=3D"font-weight=
: 400;">Follow the detailed instructions&nbsp;</span><span style=3D"letter-=
spacing: 1.2px; font-size: var( --e-global-typography-fd4917d-font-size ); =
word-spacing: var( --e-global-typography-fd4917d-word-spacing );">given bel=
ow&nbsp;</span><span style=3D"letter-spacing: var( --e-global-typography-fd=
4917d-letter-spacing ); word-spacing: var( --e-global-typography-fd4917d-wo=
rd-spacing );">while using the calculator.</span></p><h3><span id=3D"Step_1=
">Step 1</span></h3><p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">Put the function t=
hat needs to be integrated into the first box located on the right side wit=
h the label </span><b>=E2=80=9Cinterval.=E2=80=9D</b></p><h3><span id=3D"St=
ep_2">Step 2</span></h3><p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">Then enter the=
 lower and upper limits of integration in the tabs </span><b>From </b><span=
 style=3D"font-weight: 400;">and</span><b> To,&nbsp;</b><span style=3D"font=
-weight: 400;">respectively.</span></p><h3><span id=3D"Step_3">Step 3</span=
></h3><p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">The last step is to click the </=
span><b>Evaluate </b><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">button to get the fi=
nal result of the problem.</span></p><h3><span id=3D"Output">Output</span><=
/h3><p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">The output of </span><b>Simpson=E2=
=80=99s Rule Calculator</b><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;"> has multiple =
sections. The first section is the </span><b>input interpretation</b><span =
style=3D"font-weight: 400;"> where the user can cross-check that the input =
is correctly inserted.</span></p><p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">Then =
the </span><b>result</b><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;"> section displays=
 the numerical value obtained after solving the integral. Also, it provides=
 you with the </span><b>symbolic</b><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;"> form=
 of Simpson=E2=80=99s rule. Then it plots the </span><b>Error </b><span sty=
le=3D"font-weight: 400;">vs </span><b>Interval </b><span style=3D"font-weig=
ht: 400;">graph. There are two different graphs because there are two types=
 of errors.</span></p><p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">An </span><b>abs=
olute </b><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">error means the difference betw=
een the calculated and actual value while a </span><b>relative</b><span sty=
le=3D"font-weight: 400;"> is a percentage error obtained by dividing the ab=
solute error by the actual value.&nbsp;</span><span style=3D"letter-spacing=
: var( --e-global-typography-fd4917d-letter-spacing ); word-spacing: var( -=
-e-global-typography-fd4917d-word-spacing );">Lastly, it provides a detaile=
d </span><b style=3D"letter-spacing: var( --e-global-typography-fd4917d-let=
ter-spacing ); word-spacing: var( --e-global-typography-fd4917d-word-spacin=
g );">comparison</b><span style=3D"letter-spacing: var( --e-global-typograp=
hy-fd4917d-letter-spacing ); word-spacing: var( --e-global-typography-fd491=
7d-word-spacing );"> of both errors obtained using Simpson=E2=80=99s rule w=
ith errors in all other methods.</span></p><div id=3D"AdThrive_Content_3_ta=
blet" class=3D"adthrive-ad  adthrive-content adthrive-content-3" style=3D"m=
in-height: 250px;"></div><h2><span id=3D"How_Does_the_Simpson8217s_Rule_Cal=
culator_Work">How Does the Simpson=E2=80=99s Rule Calculator Work?</span></=
h2><p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">This calculator works by finding th=
e</span><b> approximate value</b><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;"> of the =
given definite integral over a specific interval. This interval is further =
divided into n subintervals of equal width.</span></p><p><span style=3D"fon=
t-weight: 400;">This calculator along with the value of the integral also c=
alculates the </span><b>relative error</b><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;"=
> bound across each interval. The working of this calculator can be acknowl=
edged by understanding the concept behind Simpson=E2=80=99s Rule.</span></p=
><h3><span id=3D"What_Is_Simpson8217s_Rule">What Is Simpson=E2=80=99s Rule?=
</span></h3><p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">Simpson=E2=80=99s rule is =
the formula that is used to approximate the</span><b> area </b><span style=
=3D"font-weight: 400;">under the curve of a function f(x) that results in f=
inding the value of the definite integral. </span><span style=3D"letter-spa=
cing: var( --e-global-typography-fd4917d-letter-spacing ); word-spacing: va=
r( --e-global-typography-fd4917d-word-spacing );">The area under the curve =
using the Riemann sum is calculated by dividing the area under the curve in=
to rectangles. However, the area under the curve is divided into </span><b =
style=3D"letter-spacing: var( --e-global-typography-fd4917d-letter-spacing =
); word-spacing: var( --e-global-typography-fd4917d-word-spacing );">parabo=
las </b><span style=3D"letter-spacing: var( --e-global-typography-fd4917d-l=
etter-spacing ); word-spacing: var( --e-global-typography-fd4917d-word-spac=
ing );">using Simpson=E2=80=99s rule.</span></p><p><span style=3D"font-weig=
ht: 400;">The definite integral is calculated by using integration techniqu=
es and by applying the limits but sometimes these techniques can not be use=
d to evaluate the integral or there is not any particular function that is =
to be integrated.</span></p><p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">Therefore,=
 Simpson=E2=80=99s rule is used to </span><b>approximate</b><span style=3D"=
font-weight: 400;"> the definite integrals in these scenarios. This rule is=
 also known as </span><b>Simpson=E2=80=99s third rule,</b><span style=3D"fo=
nt-weight: 400;"> which is written as Simpson=E2=80=99s =E2=85=93 rule.</sp=
an></p><h3><span id=3D"Simpson8217s_Rule_Formula">Simpson=E2=80=99s Rule Fo=
rmula</span></h3><p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">Simpson=E2=80=99s rul=
